s gewährt zugleich Einsichten in die vormoderne Tierkunde, die ganz andere Fragen stellte als die Zoologie unserer Zeit.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aAnimals in literature. 0aLiterature, Medieval. 7aLITERARY COLLECTIONS / Medieval.2bisacsh1 aBastert, Bernd, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrduszak, Denise, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaferland, Harald, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaubrichs, Wolfgang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHerz, Lina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKlinger, Judith, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKlingner, Judith, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKraß, Andreas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKraß, Andreas, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMüller, Jan-Dirk, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNeudeck, Otto, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRöcke, Werner, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSaurma-Jeltsch, Lieselotte E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchulz, Ronny F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWinst, Silke, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Studies 2016z9783110485264oZDB-23-DKU40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783412506582423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/